            <scopecontent>
                <p>This is a daybook of a tailor, possibly N. J. Watkins, of Annapolis, Maryland.
                    The volume dates from 1819 to 1823. Entries list customer names, items sold, and
                    amount paid. The volume also includes a section listing payments to employees.
                    There is a loose newspaper clipping inserted in the volume from 1933.</p>
            </scopecontent>


